  "text": "Found 15 key Java source files in sg-evals/kafka--0753c489 under streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/ that define the core Kafka Streams topology abstractions. The three primary entry points are: (1) Topology.java - the public class representing a directed acyclic graph (DAG) of stream processing nodes; it wraps InternalTopologyBuilder and exposes addSource, addProcessor, addSink, and addStateStore methods. (2) StreamsBuilder.java - the high-level DSL for building topologies; it wraps InternalStreamsBuilder and provides stream(), table(), and globalTable() methods that produce KStream/KTable/GlobalKTable objects. (3) KafkaStreams.java - the runtime that executes a Topology; it creates StreamThread instances, manages lifecycle (start/close), and coordinates with StreamsConfig for configuration. Supporting abstractions include: StreamsConfig.java (configuration), TopologyConfig.java (per-topology config overrides), TopologyDescription.java (interface for topology introspection), KafkaClientSupplier.java (factory interface for Kafka clients). Internal implementation classes include: InternalTopologyBuilder.java (mutable builder for processor topology), InternalStreamsBuilder.java (internal DSL builder), ProcessorTopology.java (immutable processor graph), TopologyMetadata.java (multi-topology metadata), StreamThread.java (main processing thread), and GlobalStreamThread.java (global state processing thread). Error types: TopologyException.java and StreamsException.java.",
